subSubSection.paragraph:
From 

S. midas

, 

S. ursulus

can be easily distinguished (

Fig. 
4

) in presenting 
1
) blackish hairs on the hands and feet (they are orange to ochraceous in 

S. midas

), 
2
) the intermediary stripe of dorsal hairs is bright and golden buffy (it is pale ochraceous to light grayish in 

S. midas

), 
3
) the intermediary dorsal stripe in 

S. ursulus

is 5.0–5.5 mm (it is shorter, 2.5–3.2 mm, in 

S. midas

), and 
3
) the striated hairs reach to knees, while in 

S. midas

they extend posteriorly, reaching the shank.
